ea in the grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    i, j = np.where(input_grid == green)\n    return (i[0], j[0])", "holes": {"color_black_points": "if there are non-black points on the row and column the corner is in. color all black points between the non-black point and the green corner with the color the non-black point has", "find_green_area": "find the 2*2 green area in the grid, return its left-up coordinate"}}
{"action": "edit", "code": "def color_black_points(input_grid: np.ndarray, corner: Tuple[int, int]) -> None:\n    i, j = corner\n    row = input_grid[i, :]\n    col = input_grid[:, j]\n    row_non_black = np.where(row != black)\n    col_non_black = np.where(col != black)\n    if len(row_non_black) > 1:\n        non_black_point = (row_non_black[0], j)\n        color_points_between(input_grid, non_black_point, i, j)\n        non_black_point = (row_non_black[-1], j)\n        color_points_between(input_grid, non_black_point, i, j)\n    if len(col_non_black) > 1:\n        non_black_point = (i, col_non_black[0])\n        color_points_between(input_grid, non_black_point, i, j)\n        non_black_point = (i, col_non_black[-1])\n        color_points_between(input_grid, non_black_point, i, j)\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray:\n    i, j = find_green_area(input_grid)\n    green_square = [(i, j), (i, j + 1), (i + 1, j), (i + 1, j + 1)]\n    for corner in green_square:\n        color_black_points(input_grid, corner)\n    return input_grid\ndef find_green_area(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> Tuple[int, int]:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function takes a numpy array as input and returns the left-up coordinate of the 2*2 green area in the grid.\n    \n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the grid.\n    \n    Returns:\n    A tuple of two integers representing the left-up coordinate of the 2*2 green area in the grid.\n    \"\"\"\n    i, j = np.where(input_grid == green)\n    return (i[0], j[0])\ndef color_points_between(input_grid: np.ndarray, non_black_point: Tuple[int, int], i: int, j: int) -> None:\n    \"\"\"\n    This function colors all black points between the non-black point and (i, j) with the color the non-black point has.\n    \n    Args:\n    input_grid: A numpy array representing the grid.\n    non_black_point: A tuple of two integers representing the non-black point.\n    i: An integer representing the row index of the point (i, j).\n    j: An integer representing the column index of the point (i, j).\n    \n    Returns:\n    None\n    \"\"\"\n    x, y = non_black_point\n    color = input_grid[x, y]\n    if i == x:\n        for k in range(min(j, y), max(j, y) + 1):\n            if input_grid[i, k] == black:\n                input_grid[i, k] = color\n    elif j == y:\n        for k in range(min(i, x), max(i, x) + 1):\n            if input_grid[k, j] == black:\n                input_grid[k, j] = color", "user_code": "def color_black_points(input_grid: np.ndarray, corner: Tuple[int, int]) -> None:\n    (i, j) = corner\n    row = input_grid[i, :]\n    col = input_grid[:, j]\n    row_non_black = np.where(row != black)\n    col_non_black = np.where(col != black)\n    if len(row_non_black) > 1:\n        non_black_point = (row_non_black[0],j)\n        `color all black points between the non-black point and (i, j) with the color the non-black point has`(input_grid,non_black_point,i,j)\n        non_black_point = (row_non_black[-1],j)\n        `color all black points between the non-black point and (i, j) with the color the non-black point has`(input_grid,non_black_point,i,j)\n    if len(col_non_black) > 1:\n        non_black_point = (i,col_non_black[0])\n        `color all black points between the non-black point and (i, j) with the color the non-black point has`(input_grid,non_black_point,i,j)\n        non_black_point = (i,col_non_black[-1])\n        `color all black points between the non-black point and (i, j) with the color the non-black point has`(input_grid,non_black_point,i,j)\ndef main(input_grid: np.ndarray) -> np.ndarray: \n    (i,j) = `find the 2*2 green area in the grid, return its left-up coordinate`(input_grid)\n    green_square = [(i, j), (i, j+1), (i+1, j), (i+1, j+1)]\n    for corner in green_square:\n        `if there are non-black points on the row and column the corner is in. color all black points between the non-black point and the green corner with the color the non-black point has`(input_grid,corne